    Description

    A town focused on forest creatures.

    Version

    1.00

    Author

    Agon

    http://forum.vcmi.eu/index.php

    Heroes

    Name Biography Gender Image Specialty
    Beldorn Throughout his life, Beldorn has had prophetic dreams of future events, and recently has been plagued by visions of the world's destruction. Through the art of oneiromancy, he discovered that these visions could prove true and that the key to survival lay in opening portals to a new world. male Mysticism
    Beledlen Unlike other mystics, Beledlen has a rather explosive temper, which, combined with his magical aura, affects everyone around him. This makes him a rather unusual individual among the peaceful creatures inhabiting the forest forts. His combat skills are legendary. male Blood frenzy
    Brunn Brunn was one of the first dwarves to trust Beldorn and decided to prepare for the impending doom by hoarding gold. He even tried to convince Ufretin to abandon AvLee, knowing that deep down he distrusted the elves. However, Ufretin was too loyal to his homeland. male 350 gold pieces
    Bulinar Bulinar has always had a natural talent for magic, especially combat spells. However, he is a very friendly and calm person, and so he uses his abilities only when absolutely necessary. male Sorcery
    Craig Craig has always bravely resisted the forces of both Avlee and Erathia, because, in his opinion, regardless of the fine slogans of both nations, independence is paramount. Craig is known for creating the finest armor reinforced with spells. male Armorer
    Derden Derden was originally a monk, but later noticed how everything in the world seemed to be interconnected. This resonated with him. His transition from monk to mystic, however, was so gradual that he cannot recall the day he became a forest man. male Stone skin
    Devek Devek is one of the most intelligent mystics. He has an insatiable thirst for knowledge and has perfected ancient techniques that allow him to access mana reserves greater than others can amass. He believes that the true essence of magic can be captured by combining structured knowledge with natural intuition. male Intelligence
    Dignar Dignar was raised among hobbits, despite being a dwarf himself. He was found in the forest as an infant and never met his dwarven parents. Now old, he still has a sharp mind and agile body. He teaches the hobbits how to use a sling. male Hobbits
    Drasur Drasur is one of the finest forest warriors among all dwarven mystics. He finds both melee and magical combat natural. Forest warriors and forest soldiers learn much from him. Under Drasur's watchful eye, they can run across the battlefield at incredible speeds and pounce on the enemy. male Forest warriors
    Felicia Felicia was once one of the most important druidesses of AvLee, but she rebelled against her own nation and sided with the independent peoples inhabiting the disputed lands between AvLee and Erathia. She now leads all druidesses who support independence. female Druidesses
    Kitty Kitty has earned the nickname Tremble among the sorceresses due to her supposed shyness. However, this is not entirely true, as it is the other sorceresses who avoid her rather than her. This stems from widespread envy, as she can cast spells in a much more effective than others. female -2 Spell Cost
    Laura Laura always strives for harmony and can use her innate charm and grace to win over allies. Usually, everyone willingly follows her orders. female Morale
    Narva Narva is one of the few people who managed to stop the aging process through magic and significantly increase their vitality. Her troops also benefit from her power, which has a very positive effect on reducing mortality, whether due to illness or wounds. female Fountain of Life
    Nimue Nimue enjoys the company of water nymphs and has a good relationship with them. She taught them the basics of combat and how to effectively defend their wells from intruders. female Water nymphs
    Rebecca Rebecca is one of the most famous sorceresses and participated in the War of Succession, siding with Roland. She was personally acquainted with Gem, but their paths diverged after some time. She is currently researching magic capable of overcoming any natural resistance. female Loss of Resistance
    Sayna Sayna can strengthen the weapons of her troops using ancient techniques known only to her. This mysterious sorceress has long trained in the art of blessings and water magic, and in the past, she sailed on ships, protecting them from storms and thus This is how she made her living. She now guards the forest forts. female Enchanted Weapons
    Tina Dwarf miners searching for tin pulled this hobbit girl out of a stone shell where she had been trapped for centuries. No one, including herself, knew how she got there, so the dwarves named her Tina. All that remains is to find out who she is and where she comes from. female Luck
    Velina Velina is fascinated by fire, light, and the Sun. She longs to spread warmth and a radiance that cannot be extinguished. Other sorceresses don't understand her obsession with this, but they have often seen Velina eliminate dangerous opponents from combat by blinding them with her power. female Blind
    Vianne Vianne refuses to talk about herself or her past and is angry when asked about it. Despite her secretive nature, she is a talented sorceress who can work well with others. She dreams of becoming a teacher so she can train dryads in the use of magic. female Field dryads
